# Critical Workflow Rules

- **Refactoring:**
  - Proactively refactor files exceeding 500 lines into smaller modules.
  - If provided an outdated example, modernize it (e.g., convert Class components to Functional).
- **Dependencies:** Use NPM. Prefer existing libraries over adding new ones.
- **Preserve Context:** Do not modify unrelated code. Focus strictly on the requested feature.
- **.ENV Safety:** NEVER overwrite or modify `.env` or `.env.local` files without explicit, written confirmation.

# Coding Standards

- **Naming:**
  - Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
  - Components/Classes: `PascalCase`
  - Variables/Functions: `camelCase`
- **General:** Prioritize readability and maintainability over cleverness.
- **Error Handling:** Implement try/catch blocks in async functions and use proper HTTP status codes.
- **Comments:** Add detailed comments explaining _how_ complex logic works. Avoid commenting on obvious syntax.

# Accessibility (a11y) & SEO Requirements

- **Focus:** Ensure visible focus indicators for keyboard navigation.
- **Images:** All `<img>` tags must have descriptive `alt` attributes.
- **Metadata:** Ensure proper `<title>` and `<meta name="description">` hierarchy.
- **Interactivity:** Ensure all clickable elements have `aria-label` if no text is visible.
- **Structure:** Use semantic tags (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`) instead of generic `<div>`.

# Security Best Practices

- **Validation:** Sanitize all inputs (Client & Server).
- **HTTPS:** Assume all data transit requires encryption.
- **Secrets:** Keep API keys and secrets server-side only.
- **Rate Limiting:** Implement rate limiting on API endpoints.

# Response Format

- If a file is modified, show the changes clearly or provide the full file content if it ensures safety.
- When writing code, provide the code block first, followed by a brief explanation of _why_ specific architectural decisions were made.
